leads.lead_text: Taprooted annuals or biennials; at least some leaves cauline; chiefly lowland plants
Rhizomatous perennial; leaves all radical; alps and subalps
Umbels with 20 or more flowers; mericarps usually smooth, rarely bristly; widespread, erect annual or biennial 30–120 cm high
Umbels with fewer than 15 flowers; mericarps (at least one of each pair) hirsute; short-lived mallee annuals under 30 cm high
Margins of mericarps with a pair of narrow crenate wings
Umbels 3–6-flowered; petals bluish (rarely white); both mericarps hirsute to villous with purplish bristles
Umbels 6–12-flowered; petals white; one mericarp granular-rugose but glabrous, the other with retrorsely barbellate bristles
